This paper focuses on the routing protocol for IoT networks, which is a subfield of computer networks. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also addresses the problem of DODAG created by RPL, which involves the design and analysis of distributed algorithms, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a likely category as well. The paper also evaluates the skewness of RPL trees, which involves the analysis of data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. The proposed algorithm for improving the balance of RPL trees involves optimization and control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. Finally, the paper also involves the evaluation of various routing metrics, which involves information theory and signal processing, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category.
